caption: If you're looking for an oasis in the middle of Paris, here's one! Not many urban centres have shown wisdom to protect their water bodies and green spaces. These bring healing and freshness to every day and are full of life. This one attracts a lot of joggers who, perhaps, need to discover the joys of slowing down!

Wow. Amazing. CEST bon. Beautiful. Rode through this park today. Found it to be quite amazing. Take a moment away from the tourist crowds and forest bathe. Please take your time and check out this forest. Loved it. Worth the time. There's lots of interesting scenes here. I saw in beautiful swan. Cranes and ducks
Beautiful green area beside the city area. Lots of trail running paths, walking trails for people with dogs, small little cafes, lakes etc. Mare saint James is the nicest part of this wooded area.
A perfect spot for running. Nice and soft surface with a pleny of hidden trails.

Can be very nice place. Depends when and were to visit. Today with the sun, together its lakes and small forest trails it was perfect place for a run. Also good place sunday stroll with the family. Lot of beautiful places to have picnic at summer. But scenery changes in the evenings.  And do not let kids run wild alone.  Some places has lot of use condoms lying around and people selling drugs and services for passing cars.
If your a horse racing fan this is a must,loved it,lovely stand's,great viewing plenty of eateries,if i had a moan the course announcer was very annoying and it was a bit too loud but what a visit.
Always a great pleasure to be there for my morning run . A great way to start the day

Huge jardin/parc in Paris city La Defense area. When you stay nearby you should definitely come and visit this little forest. Very refreshing and calming good and healthy for your body for your lunch and respiratory system. Despite a bit dirty (so many used condoms in certain area) and somehow itâ€™s worrisome moreover when youâ€™re a solo traveling girl. But, just waking or jogging here, or just sitting down on the bench or on the greenery grass reading book eat your packed lunch ðŸ¥ª enjoy the natural beauty and the sounds.
Very picturesque atmospheric place, worth wandering through

One of the most magical parks in Paris! I'm not sure why we waited so long to visit, but it will definitely be a priority destination for future visits. Quiet, magical feel with formal and informal gardens and park areas.

Lovely green huge spot in the heart of paris. Here you can enjoy a walk in the woods. It is well kept during day time and it is pretty safe during day time. You can walk your dog without any problem. Restaurants, activities on the lakes, workouts and many many runners. For a break I suggest you to go check this amazing park
I used it for my runs. There are sure nicer places to run
Nice place to walk, run and have a picnic.

This parc reminded me of Athens for a certain reason that I don't know! It's so beautiful with its lake, especially when it's sunny!  People walk here with their dogs, and there are a lot of ducks; a lot of animals! It's so beautiful; great vibes!

It was a bit hard ro reach and to leave with all the construction around it (from the Dauphine entrance, Septembre 2023) But once there it was so calm and beautiful, many families there or people running, it's also nice for bird watching. The huge pond had small boats to rent for a ride. At the time of this review there was also a nice small amusement park, but I think it is temporary, nice place to play or eat but the music was a bit loud

Huge park in Paris. Good for walking in the nature and doing sports outside. If you are more in a romantic mood, you can have a picnic by the lake, or rent a rowing boat. There are a few restaurants/ bars, inside the park. (The restaurants are pretty expensive). There are no public toilets inside the park. Itâ€™s also very close to: -the Louis Vuitton foundation, where you can find art expositions. - one little amusement park, good if you have kids.
Beautiful! I recommend get early in the morning to choose a spot with shade. There is a store that sells ice-cream and food and some booze but is better take your own things
One of my favorite parks. It's absolutely huge and feels like a breath of fresh air in Paris. There's some overgrown train tracks, some lakes, some beautiful places to picnic and laydown.
Massive open air play areas and woodland trails. Not very clean and properly ligthened and maintained. Parking along the road is easy though.
One of the many charming parks in Paris to enjoy your summer. The entry to park is free. you can take a stroll, enjoy the flowers, plan a picnic. For â‚¬8, enjoy boating for 30mins.
Very nice park. Lots of joggers, dog walkers - a beautiful place to enjoy a lazy Sunday afternoon walk

Difficult to enter by foot so be sure you know where you're going or you might be forced to walk through spider-web covered forest. Going here by car is highly recommended. But maybe don't bother as there's nothing here.

A splendid park with two lakes; streams, and a variety of beautiful trees â€“ some planted by Thomas Jefferson hundreds of years ago. Additionally, the odd cafe lurks about. It's a great place to spend a morning or an afternoon!

Good place to bring your kids to. Giant splash pad area for kids to play in. 5 euro admission for adults, under 3 is free. Tickets are needed for the rides and Everyone gets accounted for on them. You can renew tickets and buy new ones at various locations throughout the park.

Stunning park just outside the city. I'm so glad to have found this place, it was beautiful quite escape from the bustling and cold streets of Paris. I spent a few hours just wandering aimlessly here.
There is a small entrance fee, but the park is beautiful with nice flowers and very beautiful peacocks roaming around.  It's worth visiting just to admire the peacocks.
Iâ€™m always so happy to come here in the spring and see the nature come to life right in the middle of Paris

Great place for letting your dog run free and have the time of his life in Paris! Also nice for humans. It's big. There are some roads that cut through the green areas but not alot and not extremely busy.

Amazing place, close to the city but yet so wild. Loved the fact the there are areas for training and paths to walk, you can easily use  Google maps to get orientated. The birds' trill is just enchanting (visited in May)!
A beautiful place for a walk. Many surprises as you go in the woods. There is a lake as well and some small water falls
Best parc in Paris! Excellent for running. There is a little ile with a Chalet bar in the middle of the lake that you can reach with a little boat (2 euro round trip) .
Huge and beautiful park. Great for some peace and quite escape from a sightseeing tour. Perfect for a picknick or a bottle of wine in the evening.

I am quite sure I only saw a small part of the park, but enjoyed running here. It was quiet and peaceful. The trails were nice and wide. Since it had rained there were puddles but it allowed me to get in some grass running and jumping. ðŸ™‚ aAs it got lighter/later I saw many people walking cute dogs. It was a short run to get to the park from La Defense area. I was by myself and felt safe the whole time. I would love to explore more of the park next time.

Great alternative to Disneyland Paris ... We arrive 10:30 on a Sunday and it wasn't particularly busy.. we hardly needed to queue for rides which is great as we got to explore the whole park without much stress  Kids absolutely loved this place too and got to pet a few animals at the petting zoo

A beautiful reprise from the noise of the big city. Long unsaved alleyways, hidden little lakes with cascades and tiny streams with stone bridges help make this place magical. Itâ€™s a great place to people watch as well as they are exercising around the Lake IntÃ©rieur. Saturdays and Sundays itâ€™s packed so best to arrive on foot.

The Louis Vuitton Foundation is brilliant.  An amazing building with great shows and lighting.  Spent 1.5 hr towards the later part of day.  Need at least 3 hrs to see it properly and another 2 hours to explore the grounds around it.  The Frank Gehry building represents a boat with multiple sail.  A marvel to visit.  A must in Paris
Hands down my favorite place in Paris. Green spaces are much needed here.
Nice picnic spot ðŸ¥°we enjoyed a lot. ðŸ˜ŠMany people day spend here.ðŸ˜» â€¦
